1. download the official windows 11 image and burn it into a USB stick.
2. boot with the usb stick, start the installation process.
3. press shift-f10 to get the command prompt then type 'regedit' and add the following:
    a. HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\Setup -> add a key LabConfig
    b. inside labconfig add DWORD (32-bit)
        i. BypassTPMCheck = 1
        ii. BypassSecureBootCheck = 1
        iii. BypassRAMCheck = 1
        iv. BypassCPUCheck = 1
4. type 'list disk' then choose the right disk you want to install it to and run the following:
```
list disk
select disk 0
clean
convert gpt
create partition efi size=100
format quick fs=fat32 label="System"
create partition msr size=16
create partition primary
format quick fs=ntfs label="Windows"
exit
```
5. continue with the regular installation steps after this.
6. once windows is installed use this to activate - https://github.com/NiREvil/windows-activation
